	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree as well that there is no perfect race for Clerics.&nbsp;&nbsp;I am a level 17 Halfling and am having a blast.  I cannot believe that at higher levels it gets boring.  I find it very easy to find groups who need my help. I can solo although stuck to blue mobs and fighting one at a time then medding.  As, Clerics are not a soloing class unless of course they are soloing the undead.  I currently have 150 Wisdom and am constantly out of mana due to buffing and healing, so in that respect I can understand how folks are bored.  Sitting and medding is not fun.  However, if you want friends and want ot be liked Clerics sure do get attention.  I always get asked to join groups when I walk into a new area.  Anyway, I just wanted to give my two cents on playing a Cleric and thank everyone for thier input.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
